Read data

quantiferon <- read_csv("data/processed/vaccination_study_public/quantiferon.csv") %>% suppressMessagesAndWarnings()

serology <- read_csv("data/processed/vaccination_study_public/serology.csv") %>% suppressMessagesAndWarnings()

clinical_data <- read_csv("data/processed/vaccination_study_public/clinical_data.csv") %>% suppressMessagesAndWarnings()

antin <- read_csv("data/processed/vaccination_study_public/antinucleocapsid_data.csv") %>% suppressMessagesAndWarnings()

t5 <- read_csv("data/processed/vaccination_study_public/timepoint5_data.csv") %>% suppressMessagesAndWarnings()
become_experienced <-
  antin %>%
  filter(patid %in% (
    antin %>%
      filter(previous_result == "negative", result == "positive") %>%
      pull(patid)
  )) %>%
  filter(!is.na(timepoint_of_change)) %>%
  filter(timepoint_of_change == "T5 (last is T5)") %>%
  pull(patid)
patients_wo_neutralization_after_1st_dose <- serology %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(weeks = round(days_after_vaccination / 7)) %>%
  mutate(months = case_when(
    weeks == 0 ~ 0,
    between(weeks, 3, 4) ~ 1,
    between(weeks, 5, 6) ~ 1.5,
    between(weeks, 7, 9) ~ 2,
    between(weeks, 26, 29) ~ 6,
    between(weeks, 48, 55) ~ 12
  )) %>%
  filter(neutralization_titre == 0 & months == 1) %>%
  pull(patid)

patients_wo_neutralization_after_halfayear <- serology %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(weeks = round(days_after_vaccination / 7)) %>%
  mutate(months = case_when(
    weeks == 0 ~ 0,
    between(weeks, 3, 4) ~ 1,
    between(weeks, 5, 6) ~ 1.5,
    between(weeks, 7, 9) ~ 2,
    between(weeks, 26, 29) ~ 6,
    between(weeks, 48, 55) ~ 12
  )) %>%
  filter(neutralization_titre == 0 & months == 6) %>%
  pull(patid)

patients_wo_neutralization_before_booster <-
  intersect(patients_wo_neutralization_after_1st_dose, patients_wo_neutralization_after_halfayear)

Make separate table with cellular response data

cellular_response <- left_join(serology, clinical_data) %>%
  group_by(patid) %>%
  filter(time_point == "T4") %>%
  filter(patid %in% quantiferon$patid) %>%
  left_join(., select(quantiferon, patid, ifn_ag1, ifn_ag2)) %>%
  full_join(
    t5 %>% select(patid, time_point, igg_antispike) %>% drop_na() %>%
      inner_join(t5 %>% select(patid, time_point, neutralization_titre) %>% drop_na()) %>%
      inner_join(t5 %>% select(patid, time_point, ifn_ag1, ifn_ag2) %>% drop_na()) %>%
      left_join(., clinical_data %>% select(patid, status))
  ) %>%
  select(-date)
cellular_response <- cellular_response %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(status = ifelse(patid %in% become_experienced, "became experienced by T5", status)) %>%
  group_by(status)
# mutate(n = n(), status = case_when(status == "naive" ~ glue("naive\nn = {n}"),
#                                    status == "experienced" ~ glue("experienced\nn = {n}"),
#                                    status == "became experienced by T5" ~ glue("became experienced by T5\nn = {n}"))
#        )
cellular_response <- cellular_response %>%
  mutate(
    igg_antispike_log10 = log10(igg_antispike),
    ifn_ag2_log10 = log10(ifn_ag2),
    ifn_ag1_log10 = log10(ifn_ag1)
  )

s1 <-
  t5 %>%
  full_join(serology) %>%
  group_by(patid, time_point) %>%
  mutate(days_after_vaccination = round(mean(days_after_vaccination))) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  select(patid, time_point, days_after_vaccination) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  filter(time_point != "T0") %>%
  select(days_after_vaccination, time_point) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = days_after_vaccination, fill = time_point)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 150) +
  theme_bw(base_size = 15) +
  scale_fill_viridis_d() +

plot IgG/NT50 dynamics by months

sample_size <- reduce(list(serology, t5, clinical_data), full_join) %>%
  select(patid, status) %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  distinct() %>%
  mutate(status = ifelse(patid %in% become_experienced, "became experienced by T5", status)) %>%
  group_by(status) %>%
  summarize(n = n()) %>%
  spread(status, n) %>%
  as.list()

all_points_nt50 <-
  reduce(list(serology, t5, clinical_data), full_join) %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination), !is.na(neutralization_titre)) %>%
  mutate(status = ifelse(patid %in% become_experienced, "became experienced by T5", status)) %>%
  mutate(status = case_when(
    status == "naive" ~ glue("naive\nn = {sample_size$naive}"),
    status == "experienced" ~ glue("experienced\nn = {sample_size$experienced}"),
    status == "became experienced by T5" ~ glue("became experienced by T5\nn = {sample_size$`became experienced by T5`}")
  )) %>%
  ggplot(aes(
    x = days_after_vaccination,
    y = neutralization_titre,
    group = patid,
    fill = status
  )) +
  geom_line(alpha = 0.3, aes(color = status)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6, shape = 21, aes(color = status)) +
  theme_pubr(base_size = 10) +
  theme(legend.position = "none", axis.title.y = element_blank()) +
  xlab("# days post-vaccine") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#968974", "#D55E00", "#56B4E9")) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#968974", "#D55E00", "#56B4E9"))

mean_points_nt50 <-
  reduce(list(serology, t5, clinical_data), full_join) %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination), !is.na(neutralization_titre)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(status = ifelse(patid %in% become_experienced, "became experienced by T5", status)) %>%
  mutate(status = case_when(
    status == "naive" ~ glue("naive\nn = {sample_size$naive}"),
    status == "experienced" ~ glue("experienced\nn = {sample_size$experienced}"),
    status == "became experienced by T5" ~ glue("became experienced by T5\nn = {sample_size$`became experienced by T5`}")
  )) %>%
  mutate(weeks = round(days_after_vaccination / 7)) %>%
  select(neutralization_titre, status, weeks) %>%
  mutate(months = case_when(
    weeks == 0 ~ 0,
    between(weeks, 3, 4) ~ 1,
    between(weeks, 5, 6) ~ 1.5,
    between(weeks, 7, 9) ~ 2,
    between(weeks, 26, 29) ~ 6,
    between(weeks, 48, 55) ~ 12
  )) %>%
  filter(!is.na(months)) %>%
  select(neutralization_titre, status, months) %>%
  ggline(
    x = "months",
    y = "neutralization_titre",
    color = "status",
    add = c("median", "jitter"), shape = 15,
    palette = c("#968974", "#D55E00", "#56B4E9"),
    add.params = list(alpha = 0.3, size = 1, shape = 10), size = 1
  ) +
  theme_pubr(base_size = 10) +
  xlab("# months post-vaccine") +
  stat_compare_means(aes(group = status),
    method = "kruskal.test",
    method.args = list(alternative = "greater"),
    label = "p.signif",
    hide.ns = TRUE
  ) +
  scale_x_discrete(limits = factor(seq(0, 12, 0.5)), labels = sapply(1:length(seq(0, 12, 0.5)), function(i) ifelse(i %% 2 == 0, "", seq(0, 12, 0.5)[i]))) +
  ylab(TeX("$_{-log_{10}}$ NT50")) +
  #  annotate(geom = "text", x = 8, y = 3, label = expression("t"[1 / 2] * " = " * "45 days"), size = 4) +
  theme(legend.position = "top", legend.title = element_blank()) +
  geom_circle(aes(x0 = 13, y0 = 0, r = 0.25), inherit.aes = FALSE, size = .1) +
  annotate(geom = "text", x = 10.5, y = 0.5, label = "non-neutralizing individuals", size = 3)

get the IgG boundary value for neutralizing-after-6mths-vs-others

non_neutr_n <-
  serology %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(time_point == "T4") %>%
  pull(patid) %>%
  .[. %in% c(patients_wo_neutralization_before_booster, patients_wo_neutralization_after_halfayear)] %>%
  length()

neutr_n <- serology %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(time_point == "T4") %>%
  pull(patid) %>%
  .[!. %in% c(patients_wo_neutralization_before_booster, patients_wo_neutralization_after_halfayear)] %>%
  length()

df <-
  serology %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  filter(time_point == "T4") %>%
  transmute(
    igg_antispike = log10(igg_antispike),
    neutralization_status = as.factor(case_when(
      patid %in% c(patients_wo_neutralization_before_booster, patients_wo_neutralization_after_halfayear) ~ glue("not neutralizing\nafter half-a-year\nn = {non_neutr_n}"),
      TRUE ~ glue("neutralizing\nafter half-a-year\nn = {neutr_n}")
    ))
  )

md <- glm(neutralization_status ~ igg_antispike, data = df, family = binomial)

boundary_value <- 10^(-coef(md)[1] / coef(md)[2])

set.seed(179)
log_md <- logistic_reg()
log_fit <- log_md %>% fit(neutralization_status ~ igg_antispike, data = df)

set.seed(179)
folds <- vfold_cv(df, v = 5)
log_wf <-
  workflow() %>%
  add_model(log_md) %>%
  add_formula(neutralization_status ~ igg_antispike)

log_fit_rs <-
  log_wf %>%
  fit_resamples(folds, control = control_resamples(save_pred = TRUE))
sens_spec <- sapply(log_fit_rs$.predictions, function(x) {
  rbind(
    sens(x, estimate = .pred_class, truth = neutralization_status),
    yardstick::spec(x, estimate = .pred_class, truth = neutralization_status)
  ) %>% pull(.estimate)
})
rownames(sens_spec) <- c("sens", "spec")
colnames(sens_spec) <- paste0("cv", 1:5)

gmean <- apply(sens_spec, 2, prod) %>%
  sqrt() %>%
  mean() %>%
  round(2)
sens_spec <- t(sens_spec) %>%
  as_tibble() %>%
  transmute(
    sens_mean = mean(sens),
    sens_sd = sd(sens),
    spec_mean = mean(spec),
    spec_sd = sd(spec)
  ) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  {
    100 * .
  } %>%
  round()


p1 <-
  reduce(list(serology, t5, clinical_data), full_join) %>%
  filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination), !is.na(igg_antispike)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(
    weeks = round(days_after_vaccination / 7),
    neutralization = as.factor(case_when(
      patid %in% c(patients_wo_neutralization_before_booster, patients_wo_neutralization_after_halfayear) ~ glue("non-neutralizing\nafter 6 months\nn = {non_neutr_n}"),
      TRUE ~ glue("neutralizing\nafter 6 months\nn = {neutr_n}")
    ))
  ) %>%
  select(igg_antispike, neutralization, weeks) %>%
  mutate(
    igg_antispike = log10(igg_antispike),
    months = case_when(
      weeks == 0 ~ 0,
      between(weeks, 3, 4) ~ 1,
      between(weeks, 5, 6) ~ 1.5,
      between(weeks, 7, 9) ~ 2,
      between(weeks, 26, 29) ~ 6,
      between(weeks, 48, 55) ~ 12
    )
  ) %>%
  select(igg_antispike, neutralization, months) %>%
  ggline(
    x = "months",
    y = "igg_antispike",
    color = "neutralization",
    add = c("median", "jitter"), shape = 15,
    palette = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07", "#999999"),
    add.params = list(alpha = 0.3, size = 1, shape = 10), size = 1
  ) +
  stat_compare_means(aes(group = neutralization),
    method = "wilcox.test",
    method.args = list(alternative = "less"),
    label = "p.signif",
    hide.ns = TRUE
  ) +
  theme_pubr(base_size = 10) +
  xlab("# months post-vaccine") +
  scale_x_discrete(limits = factor(seq(0, 12, 0.5)), labels = sapply(1:length(seq(0, 12, 0.5)), function(i) ifelse(i %% 2 == 0, "", seq(0, 12, 0.5)[i]))) +
  ylab(TeX("$_{log_{10}}$ anti-S IgG $_{(BAU/ml)}$")) + theme(legend.text = element_text(size = 10), legend.title = element_text(size = 12), legend.spacing.x = unit(0.5, "cm")) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(label.position = "bottom")) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = log10(boundary_value), linetype = "dashed") +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank())

p2 <- ggplot(df, aes(x = igg_antispike, y = as.numeric(neutralization_status) - 1)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = neutralization_status), alpha = .3, size = 3, shape = 10) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07", "#999999")) +
  stat_smooth(method = "glm", se = TRUE, method.args = list(family = binomial), color = "grey50") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = log10(boundary_value), linetype = "dashed") +
  theme_pubr(base_size = 10) +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.ticks.y = element_blank(), axis.line.y = element_blank(), axis.text.y = element_blank()) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = range(p1$data$igg_antispike, na.rm = TRUE)) +
  coord_flip() +
  ylab("6 months post-vaccine") +
  scale_y_discrete(limits = c(0, 1), labels = c("", "")) +
  annotate("text", x = log10(boundary_value) - 0.3, y = 0.5, label = glue("{round(boundary_value)} BAU/ml"), size = 3) +
  annotate("text", x = 4.8, y = 0.75, label = "5-fold CV:", size = 3) +
  annotate("text",
    x = 4.4, y = 0.75,
    label = TeX(paste0("\\textit{sensitivity} = ", sens_spec$sens_mean, "\\pm{}", sens_spec$sens_sd, " %")), size = 3
  ) +
  annotate("text",
    x = 4, y = 0.75,
    label = TeX(paste0("\\textit{specificity} = ", sens_spec$spec_mean, "\\pm{}", sens_spec$spec_sd, " %")), size = 3
  ) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "none",
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank()
  )

class_separation <- vector("list", 6) %>% setNames(paste0("T", 0:5))
for (TIME_POINT in c(paste0("T", 0:5))) {
  df <-
    t5 %>%
    full_join(serology) %>%
    full_join(clinical_data) %>%
    filter(!is.na(days_after_vaccination), !is.na(igg_antispike)) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    filter(time_point == TIME_POINT) %>%
    transmute(
      igg_antispike = log10(igg_antispike),
      neutralization_status = as.factor(case_when(
        patid %in% c(patients_wo_neutralization_before_booster, patients_wo_neutralization_after_halfayear) ~ glue("non-neutralizing after 6 months\nn = {non_neutr_n}"),
        TRUE ~ glue("neutralizing after 6 months\nn = {neutr_n}")
      ))
    )

  md <- glm(neutralization_status ~ igg_antispike, data = df, family = binomial)
  boundary_value <- 10^(-coef(md)[1] / coef(md)[2])

  set.seed(179)
  log_md <- logistic_reg()
  log_fit <- log_md %>% fit(neutralization_status ~ igg_antispike, data = df)

  set.seed(179)
  folds <- vfold_cv(df, v = 5)
  log_wf <-
    workflow() %>%
    add_model(log_md) %>%
    add_formula(neutralization_status ~ igg_antispike)

  log_fit_rs <-
    log_wf %>%
    fit_resamples(folds, control = control_resamples(save_pred = TRUE))
  gmean <- sapply(log_fit_rs$.predictions, function(x) {
    rbind(
      sens(x, estimate = .pred_class, truth = neutralization_status),
      yardstick::spec(x, estimate = .pred_class, truth = neutralization_status)
    ) %>%
      pull(.estimate) %>%
      prod() %>%
      sqrt()
  }) %>%
    mean() %>%
    round(2)

  class_separation[[TIME_POINT]] <-
    ggplot(df, aes(x = igg_antispike, y = as.numeric(neutralization_status) - 1)) +
    geom_point(aes(color = neutralization_status), alpha = .3, size = 3) +
    scale_color_manual(values = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07", "#999999")) +
    stat_smooth(method = "glm", se = TRUE, method.args = list(family = binomial), color = "grey50") +
    geom_vline(xintercept = log10(boundary_value), linetype = "dashed") +
    theme_pubr(base_size = 12) +
    theme(axis.text.y = element_blank()) +
    scale_x_continuous(limits = range(p1$data$igg_antispike, na.rm = TRUE)) +
    xlab(TeX("$_{log_{10}}$ anti-S IgG $_{(BAU/ml)}$")) +
    coord_flip() +
    ggtitle(TIME_POINT) +
    annotate("text", x = log10(boundary_value) - 0.2, y = 0.5, label = glue("{round(boundary_value)} BAU/ml"), size = 4) +
    annotate("text", x = 4.6, y = 0.5, label = glue("Logistic regression on IgG at {TIME_POINT}\nG-mean metric = {gmean} (5-fold CV)"), size = 4) +
    theme(legend.position = "top", legend.title = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.title.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks.x = element_blank())
}

pmain <- function(XAXIS, YAXIS, label_xaxis, label_yaxis, legend = FALSE) {
  p <- ggscatter(datas,
    x = XAXIS, y = YAXIS,
    alpha = 0.75,
    color = "status", shape = 10,
    palette = `if`(
      length(unique(datas$status)) == 3,
      c("#968974", "#D55E00", "#56B4E9"),
      c("#D55E00", "#56B4E9")
    ),
    add = "reg.line", add.params = list(color = "status"), conf.int = FALSE
  ) +
    stat_cor(
      aes(color = status),
      method = "spearman", cor.coef.name = "rho", size = 4.5,
      digits = 2,
      label.sep = "\n",
      label.x.npc = c(0.005, 0.6),
      label.y.npc = c(0.9, 0.45)
    ) +
    theme_pubr(base_size = 12) +
    theme(legend.position = "none") +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = function(x) sprintf("%.1f", x)) #+theme(plot.margin=unit(c(0,0,-0.5,-0.5),"cm"))

  if (legend == TRUE) p <- p + theme(legend.position = "top", legend.title = element_blank())

  if (label_xaxis) {
    p <- p + xlab(ifelse(str_detect(XAXIS, "ag1"),
      TeX("$_{log_{10}}$ QuantiFERON SARS-CoV-2 Ag1"),
      TeX("$_{log_{10}}$ QuantiFERON SARS-CoV-2 Ag2")
    ))
  } else {
    p <- p + xlab("")
  }

  if (label_yaxis) {
    p <- p + ylab(ifelse(str_detect(YAXIS, "igg"),
      TeX("$_{log_{10}}$ anti-S IgG $_{(BAU/ml)}$"),
      TeX("$_{-log_{10}}$ NT50")
    ))
  } else {
    p <- p + ylab("")
  }
}

xdens <- function(PMAIN, XAXIS) {
  axis_canvas(PMAIN, axis = "x") +
    geom_density(
      data = datas,
      aes(x = datas[[XAXIS]], fill = status),
      alpha = 0.3, size = 0.2
    ) +
    theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
    fill_palette(palette = `if`(
      length(unique(datas$status)) == 3,
      c("#968974", "#D55E00", "#56B4E9"),
      c("#D55E00", "#56B4E9")
    )) #+theme(plot.margin=unit(c(-0.5,0,-0.5,-0.5),"cm"))
}
ydens <- function(PMAIN, YAXIS) {
  axis_canvas(PMAIN, axis = "y", coord_flip = TRUE) +
    geom_density(
      data = datas,
      aes(x = datas[[YAXIS]], fill = status),
      alpha = 0.3, size = 0.2
    ) +
    coord_flip() +
    theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
    fill_palette(palette = `if`(
      length(unique(datas$status)) == 3,
      c("#968974", "#D55E00", "#56B4E9"),
      c("#D55E00", "#56B4E9")
    )) #+theme(plot.margin=unit(c(0,-0.5,-0.5,0),"cm"))
}

make_plot <- function(TIME_POINT) {
  datas <<- cellular_response %>% filter(time_point == TIME_POINT)

  if (TIME_POINT == "T4") {
    datas <<- datas %>% mutate(status = ifelse(status == "became experienced by T5", "naive", status))
  } else {
    datas <<- datas %>% mutate(status = ifelse(status == "became experienced by T5", "experienced", status))
  }
  datas <<- datas %>%
    group_by(status) %>%
    mutate(n = n(), status = case_when(
      status == "naive" ~ glue("naive\nn = {n}"),
      status == "experienced" ~ glue("experienced\nn = {n}"),
      status == "became experienced by T5" ~ glue("became experienced by T5\nn = {n}")
    ))
  pmain_ag1_igg <- pmain("ifn_ag1_log10", "igg_antispike_log10", FALSE, TRUE, TRUE) + ylim(1.75, 3.75)
  plot_legend <- get_legend(pmain_ag1_igg)
  pmain_ag1_igg <-
    pmain("ifn_ag1_log10", "igg_antispike_log10", FALSE, TRUE) +
    xlim(-1.5, 1.05) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = label_number(accuracy = 0.1), limits = `if`(TIME_POINT == "T4", c(1.75, 3.75), c(2.5, 5)))
  pmain_ag2_igg <-
    pmain("ifn_ag2_log10", "igg_antispike_log10", FALSE, FALSE) +
    xlim(-1.5, 1.05) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = label_number(accuracy = 0.1), limits = `if`(TIME_POINT == "T4", c(1.75, 3.75), c(2.5, 5)))
  pmain_ag1_nt50 <-
    pmain("ifn_ag1_log10", "neutralization_titre", TRUE, TRUE) +
    xlim(-1.5, 1.05) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = label_number(accuracy = 0.1), limits = `if`(TIME_POINT == "T4", c(0, 3), c(2, 4.5)))
  pmain_ag2_nt50 <-
    pmain("ifn_ag2_log10", "neutralization_titre", TRUE, FALSE) +
    xlim(-1.5, 1.05) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = label_number(accuracy = 0.1), limits = `if`(TIME_POINT == "T4", c(0, 3), c(2, 4.5)))
  xdens_ag1 <- xdens(pmain_ag1_igg, "ifn_ag1_log10")
  xdens_ag2 <- xdens(pmain_ag2_igg, "ifn_ag2_log10")
  ydens_igg <- ydens(pmain_ag1_igg, "igg_antispike_log10")
  ydens_nt50 <- ydens(pmain_ag2_nt50, "neutralization_titre")

  pmain_ag1_igg <- insert_xaxis_grob(pmain_ag1_igg, xdens_ag1, grid::unit(.1, "null"), position = "top")
  pmain_ag2_igg <- insert_xaxis_grob(pmain_ag2_igg, xdens_ag2, grid::unit(.1, "null"), position = "top")
  pmain_ag2_igg <- insert_yaxis_grob(pmain_ag2_igg, ydens_igg, grid::unit(.1, "null"), position = "right")
  pmain_ag2_nt50 <- insert_yaxis_grob(pmain_ag2_nt50, ydens_nt50, grid::unit(.1, "null"), position = "right")
  p1 <- ggarrange(
    as_ggplot(plot_legend),
    ggarrange(
      pmain_ag1_igg, pmain_ag2_igg,
      pmain_ag1_nt50, pmain_ag2_nt50,
      widths = c(1, 1.075)
    ),
    ncol = 1, heights = c(0.1, 2)
  )
  p1
}

  labels = c("T4", "T5"),
  font.label = list(size = 12, face = c("bold.italic"))
)

      df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("naive"),
      df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("became"),
      df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("experienced\n")
    )
  ),
  y = value,
  fill = factor(status,
    levels = c(
      df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("naive"),
      df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("became"),
      df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("experienced\n")
    )
  )
)) +
  facet_wrap(~name,
    scales = "free",
    labeller = label_parsed
  ) +
  geom_violin(draw_quantiles = 0.5) +
  geom_beeswarm(alpha = 0.5) +
  # geom_boxplot(width = 0.1, color = "black", alpha = 0.3, size=0.75) +
  stat_compare_means(
    method = "wilcox.test", size = 4,
    label = "p.signif",
    comparisons = {
      df$status %>%
        unique() %>%
        combn(2, simplify = FALSE)
    }
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))) +
  xlab(element_blank()) +
  ylab(element_blank()) +
  theme_pubr() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#56B4E9", "#968974", "#D55E00")) +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
    legend.title = element_blank()
  ) +
  ggtitle("Response to the booster (T5 - T4)")

df <-
  serology %>%
  mutate(igg_antispike_log10 = log10(igg_antispike)) %>%
  filter(time_point %in% c("T0", "T1")) %>%
  group_by(patid) %>%
  filter(n() > 1) %>%
  arrange(time_point, .by_group = TRUE) %>%
  mutate(
    first_diff_nt50 = diff(neutralization_titre),
    first_diff_igg = diff(igg_antispike_log10)
  ) %>%
  slice_head() %>%
  select(patid, starts_with("first")) %>%
  inner_join(
    cellular_response %>%
      filter(time_point %in% c("T4", "T5")) %>%
      group_by(patid) %>%
      filter(n() > 1) %>%
      arrange(time_point, .by_group = TRUE) %>%
      mutate(
        booster_diff_nt50 = diff(neutralization_titre),
        booster_diff_igg = diff(igg_antispike_log10),
        status = factor(status, levels = c("naive", "became experienced by T5", "experienced"))
      ) %>%
      select(patid, starts_with("booster"), sex, age, smoking, BMI, status) %>%
      slice_head() %>%
      group_by(status) %>%
      mutate(status = glue("{status}\nn={n()}"))
  ) %>%
  mutate(status = factor(status, levels = c(
    df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("naive"),
    df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("became"),
    df$status %>% unique() %>% str_subset("experienced\n")
  )))
